# Rule 00 — PrimeVue Ecosystem Guardrails

AI agents frequently (a) reach for native HTML elements instead of PrimeVue components, (b) hallucinate prop/event/slot names from outdated training data, and (c) use `:deep()` CSS overrides instead of the PT system. This rule enforces three pillars of defense.

> **Stack**: PrimeVue v4.5+ Styled Mode. All components are auto-imported (core Rule 07).
> **Companion rule**: For PT styling methodology → `01-primevue-pt-styling.mdc`.

---

## PILLAR 1 — Strict Component Substitution

### 1.1 ABSOLUTE RULE

In `src/views/`, `src/components/`, and `src/layouts/`, native HTML interactive/data/feedback elements are **FORBIDDEN** when a PrimeVue equivalent exists.

When a project Pro-wrapper equivalent exists, direct raw PrimeVue usage is also **FORBIDDEN**:
- `<DataTable>` / `<Column>` in business pages -> use `<ProTable>`
- raw business `<Dialog>` / `<Drawer>` declarations -> use `useDialog` + `PrimeDialog`
- multi-field business form built from raw controls -> use `<ProForm :schema>`

**Permitted native elements** (structural/semantic only): `<div>`, `<span>`, `<section>`, `<header>`, `<footer>`, `<main>`, `<nav>`, `<aside>`, `<article>`, `<ul>`, `<ol>`, `<li>`, `<label>`, `<form>`, `<h1>`–`<h6>`, `<p>`, `<a>` (external links only — internal navigation MUST use `<RouterLink>`).

**[LAW] Form Sovereignty:**
Inside `src/views/**` (Business Pages), native `<form>` is FORBIDDEN. MUST use `<ProForm>` for forms with 2+ fields. Single-field trivial cases may use standalone PrimeVue controls.

### 1.2 Complete Substitution Table

> Source of truth: `src/types/components.d.ts` (auto-generated registry).

| FORBIDDEN Native Element | REQUIRED PrimeVue v4 Component | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| `<button>` | `<Button>` | `severity`, `text`, `outlined`, `icon` props |
| `<input type="text">` | `<InputText>` | |
| `<input type="number">` | `<InputNumber>` | `mode`, `min`, `max`, `step` |
| `<input type="checkbox">` | `<Checkbox>` | Binary: boolean `v-model`; Group: array |
| `<input type="radio">` | `<RadioButton>` | Always in a group with shared `v-model` |
| `<textarea>` | `<Textarea>` | `autoResize` prop available |
| `<select>` / `<option>` | `<Select>` | **v4 name** (NOT `Dropdown`) |
| `<input type="date">` | `<DatePicker>` | **v4 name** (NOT `Calendar`) |
| `<input type="range">` | `<Slider>` | |
| `<input type="password">` | `<Password>` | Built-in strength meter |
| `<input type="file">` | `<FileUpload>` | |
| `<table>` / `<thead>` / `<tbody>` / `<tr>` / `<td>` / `<th>` | `<DataTable>` + `<Column>` | Or `<ProTable>` for project tables |
| `<dialog>` | `<Dialog>` | Or `useDialog()` composable |
| `<progress>` | `<ProgressBar>` | |
| `<details>` / `<summary>` | `<Accordion>` + `<AccordionPanel>` + `<AccordionHeader>` + `<AccordionContent>` | v4 compound component API |
| `<fieldset>` | `<Fieldset>` | |
| Toggle/switch checkbox | `<ToggleSwitch>` | **v4 name** (NOT `InputSwitch`) |
| `<img>` (zoomable) | `<Image>` | Bare `<img>` OK for simple static display |
| `<a>` (internal navigation) | `<RouterLink>` | Not PrimeVue, but REQUIRED for SPA nav |

### 1.3 v3 → v4 Name Migration Guard

> **Silent-fail risk**: v3 names compile without errors but render **nothing** because no component is registered under the old name.

| v3 Name (FORBIDDEN) | v4 Name (REQUIRED) |
|---|---|
| `Dropdown` | `Select` |
| `Calendar` | `DatePicker` |
| `InputSwitch` | `ToggleSwitch` |
| `Sidebar` | `Drawer` |
| `TabView` / `TabPanel` (monolithic) | `Tabs` + `TabList` + `Tab` + `TabPanels` + `TabPanel` |
| `Steps` (monolithic) | `Stepper` + `StepList` + `Step` + `StepPanels` + `StepPanel` |

### 1.4 Permitted Exceptions

1. **System configuration demo pages** (`src/views/system-configuration/`) — native elements permitted for design token visualization that intentionally operates outside PrimeVue.
2. **Custom ProForm field wrappers** (`packages/vue-ui/src/ProForm/renderers/components/`) — may use native elements for fine-grained internal control.

These exceptions do NOT extend to business pages or general components.

### 1.5 🚨 Internal Abstraction Mandates (CRITICAL)

- **Feedback Channel (ABSOLUTE RULE):** NEVER use raw PrimeVue `Toast` instances in business code and NEVER use native `alert` / `confirm` for user feedback. You MUST route feedback through the internal abstraction (`@/components/ProToast` or the project's configured toast service APIs such as `window.$toast` / `window.$message`) to preserve queue policy, theme consistency, and cross-module UX behavior.
- **Dialogs (ARCHITECTURAL PRIORITY):** Prefer the internal dialog abstraction (`@/components/PrimeDialog` or equivalent architecture-approved wrapper / `useDialog`) over raw PrimeVue `Dialog` declarations when implementing business dialogs, so lifecycle orchestration, layout constraints, and close behaviors remain centralized.
- **Scrolling (GLOBAL SSOT):** Cross-reference `02-pro-components.mdc`. All scrollable regions MUST use `<CScrollbar>`. **STRICT PROHIBITION:** NEVER use `overflow-auto` or `overflow-scroll` on generic containers for primary page scrolling. Use `<CScrollbar class="col-fill">...</CScrollbar>` as the canonical pattern.

