## PILLAR 3 — PT Styling Mandate

### 3.1 PT-First Principle

All visual customization of PrimeVue components MUST use the Pass-Through (`pt`) system. See `01-primevue-pt-styling.mdc` for the complete methodology, token reference, and correct patterns.

### 3.2 `:deep()` Prohibition — Exhaustive Exception List

`:deep(.p-*)` targeting PrimeVue internal classes is **FORBIDDEN** in business code. Exactly three files have documented exceptions:

1. **`packages/vue-ui/src/ProTable/ProTable.vue`** — DataTable frozen column z-index management, row selection coloring, and grid line control. These are CSS-variable overrides that cannot be expressed via PT.
2. **`apps/web-demo/src/views/login/index.vue`** — Card transparency for glassmorphism effect.
3. **`src/layouts/components/AnimateRouterView.vue`** — Animation library class positioning.

Any NEW `:deep(.p-*)` usage requires explicit architectural justification and MUST be added to this exception list.

### 3.3 Global PT Presets — Check Before Writing

Before writing any local `:pt` prop, check if a global preset already covers the component:

- `src/utils/theme/ptPresets/formControlsPt.ts` — InputText, InputNumber, InputChips, Password, Textarea, DatePicker, Select, MultiSelect, AutoComplete, SelectButton
- `src/utils/theme/ptPresets/menuPt.ts` — TieredMenu, PanelMenu
- `src/utils/theme/presetComponents/` — Preset-level styling for all component categories (base, form, overlay, data, menuNavMisc)

If a global PT exists, your local `:pt` should only **ADD** classes, not **DUPLICATE** or **CONFLICT** with the global preset.

